comments: Kleber (DAL) swipes forward and cleanly dislodges the ball away from White (SAS) during the drive.
White's (SAS) leg touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) and White (SAS) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and absorbs the contact.

Hardaway Jr. (DAL) stops short of White (SAS) as he contests the jump shot attempt and the marginal follow-through contact occurs as a result of White's leg extending toward Hardaway Jr.'s lower half.
Johnson (SAS) cleanly deflects the pass intended for Hardaway Jr. (DAL) before incidental arm contact occurs.
Murray (SAS) moves forward toward Brunson (DAL) and marginal body contact occurs as Brunson is passing.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Johnson's (SAS) path and absorbs the contact. Kleber and Johnson briefly engage and disengage thereafter.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes a legal guarding position in Doncic's (DAL) path and he absorbs the oncoming contact.
Vassell (SAS) makes incidental body contact with Brunson (DAL) as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Brunson (DAL) continues moving toward the sideline following the hand-off and incidental body contact occurs with Poeltl (SAS).
Murray's (SAS) right leg is extended outward when marginal body contact occurs with Doncic (DAL) as Doncic starts his drive.
Vassell (SAS) delivers body contact to Doncic (DAL) that affects his driving shot attempt.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes a wide screening position in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and delivers contact to Hardaway Jr. that affects his ability to defend.
Murray (SAS) briefly has his arm around Doncic's (DAL) upper half and quickly slides it off.
Murray (SAS) reaches in and makes contact to Doncic's (DAL) arm that affects his ability to maintain control of the ball during his drive.
Kleber (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position as contact occurs with Murray (SAS) beyond the perimeter.
Kleber (DAL) brushes Murray's (SAS) right arm and marginal contact occurs as Murray secures the rebound.
Doncic (DAL) jumps and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs with Murray (SAS) following the release of his shot attempt near the rim.
Murray (SAS) raises both of his hands during rebounding and marginal contact occurs with Finney-Smith's (DAL) right arm as he back-taps the ball.
Poeltl (SAS) commits a take foul on Bullock (DAL).
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and gives Hardaway Jr. a step of distance to avoid the contact, which Poeltl absorbs.
Kleber (DAL) brings his arm down and initiates contact across Johnson's (SAS) arm during the driving shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) enters the lane prior to the free throw attempt making contact with the rim.
Poeltl (SAS) commits a take foul on Finney-Smith (DAL).
Poeltl (SAS) and Kleber (DAL) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
